Trevor Noah attends the 50th NAACP Image Awards at Dolby Theatre on March 30, 2019 in Hollywood, California. JOHANNESBURG - The Daily Show host Trevor Noah made history over the weekend as the first African comedian to sell out Madison Square Garden. Noah, who is currently on his Loud and Clear Tour, shared several pictures from the night on social media and thanked fans for their support. READ: Trevor Noah fourth highest paid comedian in the world: Forbes "Last night was incredible! Thank you to everyone that packed out @thegarden and made it such a memorable night! 🙏🏾 I didn’t want it to end", read the caption. Tickets for the worldwide tour are available on trevornoah.com. Last night was incredible! Thank you to everyone that packed out  @thegarden and made it such a memorable night! 🙏🏾 I didn’t want it to end. 📷: @marklashark #LoudAndClearWorldTour A post shared by  Trevor Noah (@trevornoah) on Nov 9, 2019 at 2:47pm PST Ticket pre-sale is happening now! 40+ new dates. Find tickets on my website TrevorNoah.com (link in bio) 🙌🏾#LoudAndClearWorldTour 🌎 A post shared by  Trevor Noah (@trevornoah) on Nov 6, 2019 at 11:17am PST